==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tractor propeller
<hw>Tractor propeller</hw>
}</mhw>. <fld>(Aviation)</fld> <def>A propeller screw placed in front of
the supporting planes of an airplane instead of behind them, so that it
exerts a pull instead of a push. Hence, <col><b>Tractor
monoplane</b></col>, <col><b>Tractor biplane</b></col>, etc. This is the
most common arrangement for propellers on modern airplanes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tractor-trailer</ent>⟦br⟧
